source('XGBoost.R')
source('LogitBoost.R')

Create dataset.

x1 = (1: 1000)/100 - 5
Y = as.integer(exp(x1)/(1 + exp(x1)) > 0.4)
dataset <- data.frame("X1"= x1, "y"= Y)
dataset[c(12, 120, 121, 123, 128, 183, 252, 444, 333, 389),  "y"] <- 1
dataset[c(756:787),  "y"] <- 0


plot(dataset$X1, 
      dataset$y, 
      col='green',
      main="Dataset")

Train LogitBoost model.

eta_list = c(0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)
for (eta in eta_list) {
  fit_lb <- logitboost(input_formula = y ~ X1,
                       dataset = dataset,
                       hiperparms = list(eta = eta,
                                         n_trees = 20))
  
   y_pred <- predict(fit_lb,
                   dataset = dataset)

  plot(dataset$X1, 
       dataset$y, 
       col='green',
       main=paste("Logit Boost - trees: ", 20, 
                  '  step_size: ', eta,
                  sep=''))
  lines(dataset$X1, y_pred)
}

Train XGBoost model.

fit <- xgboost(input_formula = y ~ X1,
                  dataset = dataset,
                  task_type = 'classification',
                  hiperparms = list(eta = 0.3,
                                    lambda = 0,
                                    gamma = 0, 
                                    n_trees = 20))

y_pred <- predict(fit,
                  dataset = dataset)

plot(dataset$X1, 
     dataset$y, 
     col='green',
     main=paste("Gradient Boost - trees: ", 20, 
                  '  step_size: ', eta,
                  sep=''))
lines(dataset$X1, y_pred)

Fitting a model with different hiperparmeters

eta_list = c(0.1, 0.5, 1)
lambda_list = c(0.1, 1, 5)
gamma_list = c(0.1, 1, 5)
trees_list = c(5, 20, 50)

for (eta in eta_list) {
  for (lambda in lambda_list) {
    for (gamma in gamma_list) {
      for (trees in trees_list) {
        fit <- xgboost(input_formula = y ~ X1, 
               dataset = dataset, 
               task_type = 'classification',
               hiperparms = list(eta = eta, 
                                 lambda = lambda,
                                 gamma = gamma, 
                                 n_trees = trees))
         y_pred <- predict(fit,
                   dataset = dataset)

        plot(dataset$X1, 
             dataset$y, 
             col='green',
             main=paste("XGBoost - trees: ", trees, 
                    '  lambda: ', lambda,
                    '  gamma: ', gamma,
                    '  step_size: ', eta,
                    sep=''))
        lines(dataset$X1, y_pred)
      }
    }
    
  }
}
